# API & Server Action rules

Keep handlers **thin** — validate input, call `src/lib/domain/` (or `src/lib/settings/` / `src/lib/integrations/`), map errors to action responses.

## Auth

- Every Server Action starts with `getTasksUser()` from `src/lib/access.ts` and returns `{ error }` when it fails — copy the `requireUser()` helper pattern in `src/app/actions/tasks.ts`.
- Board/task-level checks via `requireWorkspaceEdit` / `requireTaskEdit` (`src/lib/domain/task-authz.ts`) after the app gate.
- Cron routes: `isAuthorizedCronRequest(request)` (`src/lib/cron-auth.ts`) → 401 before anything else.
- Never import edge-incompatible `src/lib/auth.ts` in `middleware.ts` — use `src/lib/auth.config.ts`.

## Validation

- FormData fields are trimmed and checked inline; enums parsed against Prisma enums (`parsePriority`, `parseLinkedApp`) — return `{ error: "…" }` for bad input, don't throw.
- Config/env is read via `src/lib/tasks-config.ts` and direct `process.env` in crons (no zod in this repo).

## Responses

- Server Actions return `ActionResult = { error?: string, … }` — user-facing message, no stack traces.
- Call `revalidatePath()` for every affected route after a write (inbox `/`, board `/boards/[id]`, list view).
- API routes return `NextResponse.json`; cron handlers report `{ ok, sent/skipped }`.

## Cron routes (see vercel.json)

- `/api/cron/task-digest` — weekdays 07:00 UTC, org-wide Slack digest to `SLACK_TASK_DIGEST_WEBHOOK_URL`.
- `/api/cron/personal-slack-digest` — weekdays 07:00 UTC, per-user digests to each user's own webhook.
- New REST endpoints only for cron / health / auth — everything else is a Server Action.

## Do NOT

- Put business rules inline in route handlers
- Skip auth on routes exposed to the internet
- Return stack traces to clients in production
